## 5) Dual-Track Sprint Model

### Track A: Execution (current sprint)

AI agents execute the current sprint's tasks per the specs above. The orchestrator manages the executor→reviewer loop. HitM verifies V3 items only.

### Track B: Planning (next sprint)

While Track A executes, HitM (or a planning AI like Antigravity) writes detailed task specs for the **next** sprint. This means:

```
Sprint N executing (Track A)          Sprint N+1 planning (Track B)
┌─────────────────────────────┐      ┌──────────────────────────────┐
│ Executor AI: code per spec  │      │ HitM + Antigravity:          │
│ Reviewer AI: verify per V   │      │   - Write end-state specs    │
│ Orchestrator: manage loop   │      │   - Pre-lock decisions       │
│ HitM: V3 verification only  │      │   - Define scope locks       │
│                             │      │   - Author anti-patterns     │
│                             │      │   - Create slice breakdown   │
└─────────────────────────────┘      └──────────────────────────────┘
         ↓ Sprint N complete                    ↓ Specs ready
         ════════════════════════════════════════
                    Sprint N+1 begins immediately
                    (no planning delay between sprints)
```

### Track B deliverables (ready before Sprint N completes)

For each task in the next sprint:
- [ ] `tasks/T##_<slug>.md` — full spec per §1 format
- [ ] `DECISION_LOG.md` — pre-populated with architectural decisions
- [ ] `runtime_handoff.md` — initialized with branch state and slice catalog
- [ ] Orchestration handoffs drafted in `plans/pipeline_queue/`
- [ ] READ FIRST paths verified (all files exist)

