## 6) Periodic QA Sweeps (Biweekly)

Every other week during active development, run dedicated QA passes:

### Security Sweep

```markdown
# Security Sweep — <Date>

## Scope
- All files changed since last sweep (git diff --name-only <last-sweep-sha>..HEAD)

## Checklist
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets, tokens, or API keys
- [ ] All user input is validated/sanitized before use
- [ ] All API endpoints check authentication and authorization
- [ ] No SQL injection vectors (raw queries, string interpolation)
- [ ] No XSS vectors (dangerouslySetInnerHTML, unescaped user content)
- [ ] CORS configuration is restrictive (not wildcard)
- [ ] Sensitive data not logged (passwords, tokens, PII)
- [ ] Dependencies checked for known vulnerabilities (npm audit / safety)
- [ ] File upload handling (if any) validates type and size

## Findings
| ID | Severity | File | Issue | Fix |
|----|----------|------|-------|-----|
```

### Optimization Sweep

```markdown
# Optimization Sweep — <Date>

## Scope
- All files changed since last sweep

## Checklist
- [ ] No N+1 query patterns in API views
- [ ] select_related/prefetch_related used where appropriate
- [ ] No unnecessary re-renders in React components
- [ ] Bundle size check: no unexpectedly large imports
- [ ] API response times: no endpoint >500ms under normal load
- [ ] Database indexes exist for frequently queried fields
- [ ] No blocking I/O in request handlers

## Findings
| ID | Category | File | Issue | Impact | Fix |
|----|----------|------|-------|--------|-----|
```

### Code Quality Sweep

```markdown
# Code Quality Sweep — <Date>

## Scope
- All files changed since last sweep

## Checklist
- [ ] No file exceeds 500 lines (soft ceiling per GEMINI.md golden rule 3)
- [ ] Separation of concerns: no view files containing business logic
- [ ] Consistent naming conventions across new code
- [ ] No dead code or commented-out blocks left from debugging
- [ ] Test coverage exists for new business logic
- [ ] CHANGELOG.md updated for all behavior changes
- [ ] No TODO/FIXME without linked issue or plan ID

## Findings
| ID | Category | File | Issue | Fix |
|----|----------|------|-------|-----|
```

### Sweep cadence and ownership

| Week | Activity | Owner |
|------|----------|-------|
| Sprint week 1 | Feature execution | Executor AI + Reviewer AI |
| Sprint week 2 | Feature execution continues | Executor AI + Reviewer AI |
| Sweep week | Security + Optimization + Quality sweeps | Dedicated QA AI agent (or HitM) |
| Sprint week 3 | Feature execution resumes | Executor AI + Reviewer AI |

Sweep results are filed in `plans/S1/S1.B/qa-sweeps/<date>/` and any findings become tasks in the current or next sprint.

---

## Pipeline final gate (D2 — mandatory WS3 drain)

WS3 review drain is a mandatory pipeline gate, not a follow-up. Cursor may not call
`queue_done`, mark a task complete, or produce a status report implying merge-readiness while
any PR opened for that task remains PENDING in `review.queue`. Run `ws_review.sh` (or
`codex_review.sh` directly) before closing the task. Stage N does not start while Stage N-1
gate is open. Status reports must label Cursor-owned blocking work as **BLOCKING**, not as
"follow-up for HitM."

---

## Adoption

- **Immediate:** All new task specs must follow §1 format.
- **Existing plans:** Retrofit task files to include End State, Scope Lock, and Anti-Patterns before next execution.
- **Sprint planning:** HitM or planning AI writes specs per §2 quality bar — "implementable without questions."
- **QA sweeps:** Begin biweekly cadence when full development resumes (~July 2026).
